cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.DL, cs.HC, cs.NI 

The paper discusses the challenge of providing a high-quality search experience on Mars, which involves formulating the searching from Mars problem as a tradeoff between "effort" and "data transfer". This problem is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and distributed computing (cs.DC), as well as data caching and pre-fetching (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper touches on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) as it explores the user experience and the physical limitations of data transfer.
